"title": "1349: covenant, God's at Sinai",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1349: covenant, god's at sinai",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God's faithful commitment, made in pursuance of his promises to Abraham, to acknowledge the newly-redeemed Israel as his own special people. Israel's required response to the grace of God in election was to be holiness and obedience to the law.</p>\n<h2>The occasion of the covenant</h2>\n<h3>The covenant fulfilled God's promises to Abraham</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:12-Deut29:13\">DEU 29:12–29:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:24\">EXO 2:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:4-Exod6:8\">EXO 6:4–6:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:8\">DEU 7:8</a></p>\n<h3>The covenant followed Israel's redemption from slavery</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer34:13\">JER 34:13</a></strong> <em>God's covenant at Sinai was made in the context of his historical acts of deliverance. Covenants (“treaties”) between a supreme (suzerain) overlord and a subordinate ruler (vassal) are well known in ancient Near Eastern writings.  They are not “agreements” but “requirements”.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:2\">EXO 20:2</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:6\">DEU 5:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:45\">LEV 26:45</a></p>\n<h3>The covenant was mediated through Moses</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:27\">EXO 34:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:46\">LEV 26:46</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:1\">DEU 29:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:17\">JHN 1:17</a></p>\n<h3>The covenant was accompanied by signs of God's presence</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:18-Exod19:19\">EXO 19:18–19:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:18-Exod20:19\">EXO 20:18–20:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:16\">EXO 24:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:8\">PSA 68:8</a></p>\n<h2>Sealing the covenant</h2>\n<h3>Sharing a meal</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:11\">EXO 24:11</a></p>\n<h3>Offering a sacrifice</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:5-Exod24:8\">EXO 24:5–24:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps50:5\">PSA 50:5</a></p>\n<h3>God's oath</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:9\">DEU 28:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:14\">DEU 29:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:8\">EZK 16:8</a></p>\n<h3>Israel's promise</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:8\">EXO 19:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:3\">EXO 24:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:7\">EXO 24:7</a></p>\n<h2>The covenant relationship</h2>\n<h3>Israel as God's people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:6\">DEU 7:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:5-Exod19:6\">EXO 19:5–19:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:12\">LEV 26:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:2\">DEU 14:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer13:11\">JER 13:11</a></p>\n<h3>Israel adopted into God's family</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:1\">HOS 11:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:30-Deut1:31\">DEU 1:30–1:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:5\">DEU 8:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa63:16\">ISA 63:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:10\">MAL 2:10</a></p>\n<h3>Israel as God's bride</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:2\">JER 2:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:5-Isa54:8\">ISA 54:5–54:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:32\">JER 31:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:8\">EZK 16:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:14-Hos2:16\">HOS 2:14–2:16</a></p>\n<h2>The blessings of the covenant</h2>\n<h3>Inheriting God's promises</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:3\">DEU 6:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut26:18-Deut26:19\">DEU 26:18–26:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:9\">DEU 28:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh23:5\">JOS 23:5</a></p>\n<h3>Provision and protection</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:3-Lev26:13\">LEV 26:3–26:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:1-Deut28:14\">DEU 28:1–28:14</a> <em>This pattern of blessings and curses is also a feature of Near Eastern political treaties.</em></p>\n<h2>The requirements of the covenant</h2>\n<h3>Obedience to the law</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:7\">EXO 24:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:27-Exod34:28\">EXO 34:27–34:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:13\">DEU 4:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh8:31\">JOS 8:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh8:1\">NEH 8:1</a></p>\n<h3>Holiness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:2\">DEU 14:2</a></strong> <em>Israel has been made holy through her election as the covenant people of God. The ensuing call for holiness is a call to work out the implications of that relationship and to live in accordance with its demands</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:45\">LEV 11:45</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:26\">LEV 20:26</a></p>\n<h3>Wholehearted devotion</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:14\">EXO 34:14</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:12\">DEU 10:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:32\">EXO 23:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:23\">DEU 4:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:5\">DEU 6:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:20\">DEU 10:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh24:14-Josh24:15\">JOS 24:14–24:15</a></p>\n<h2>Breaking the covenant</h2>\n<h3>The consequences of breaking the covenant</h3>\n<p>Disease:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:15-Lev26:16\">LEV 26:15–26:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:21-Deut28:22\">DEU 28:21–28:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:19-Lev26:20\">LEV 26:19–26:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:23-Deut28:24\">DEU 28:23–28:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:17\">LEV 26:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:25\">LEV 26:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:25\">DEU 28:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:32-Lev26:33\">LEV 26:32–26:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:36-Deut28:37\">DEU 28:36–28:37</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh23:16\">JOS 23:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek17:19-Ezek17:20\">EZK 17:19–17:20</a></p>\n<h3>Israel's unfaithfulness to the covenant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:37\">PSA 78:37</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:12\">2KI 18:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr5:25\">1CH 5:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:8\">JER 3:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer11:10\">JER 11:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:32\">EZK 16:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos6:7\">HOS 6:7</a></p>\n<h2>God's commitment to the covenant</h2>\n<h3>God's covenant of love</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:9\">DEU 7:9</a></strong> <em>“love” translates the Hebrew word “hesed”, which here expresses God's loyalty and faithful commitment to his covenant people.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:5\">NEH 1:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:4\">DAN 9:4</a></p>\n<h3>The everlasting covenant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:60\">EZK 16:60</a></strong> <em>God's faithfulness to the covenant at Sinai will result in a new covenant that will never come to an end.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:8\">ISA 61:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:40\">JER 32:40</a></p>\n<h2>Renewing the covenant</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:40-Lev26:45\">LEV 26:40–26:45</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:1\">DEU 29:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh24:22-Josh24:25\">JOS 24:22–24:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:3\">2KI 23:3</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr34:31\">2CH 34:31</a></p>",
